==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[kilomètre]] < Greek [[χίλιοι]] ('[[thousand]]') + [[μέτρον]].

===Alternative spellings===
*(''US'') [[kilometer]]

===Noun===
'''kilometre''' (''British and Canadian spelling''; ''plural:'' '''kilometres''')

#An [[SI#Abbreviation|SI]]/MKS unit of measure equal to one thousand [[metre]]s.

====Symbol====
*[[km]] (''official [[SI]] symbol''), [[Km]] (''chiefly American, in non-scientific usage, such as in road signs'')

